    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 815.51/169 b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: As the Counsellor of our
                    Embassy was told last evening, I yesterday signed with General Paredes, the
                    Special Minister of Honduras, a convention to secure the loan which it is
                    expected will in the near future be made to refund the debt of <pb facs="0671"
                        n="555" xml:id="pg_555"/> Honduras, and in view of the interest of the
                    Council of Foreign Bondholders, I have cabled our Embassy at London to give this
                    information to the British Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
